records.Name: Boys & Girls Clubs of Philadelphia - Northeast Frankford Club
records.Launchpad__Job_Description__c: During the Summer Work-Based Learning program, youth ages 14-17 will have an opportunity to learn more about Boys &Girls Clubs of Philadelphia while supporting summer camp programs and activities. Guided by experienced staff members, youth will learn about BGCP 's role in the community, help lead summer camp activities, and serve as positive role models for younger campers. Participants will gain valuable work experience, professional skills, and a chance to work with children in their community. Serving all youth; specially in the North, Northeast areas.

records.Name: Heights - Community Partnership School
records.Launchpad__Job_Description__c: The Academy program provides rigorous learning opportunities to high-achieving students attending top-performing independent schools in Philadelphia. The program begins our long-term relationship with scholars as rising 5th-8th graders through the summer and school year programs. The program develops scholars? critical thinking, writing, and reading skills through our math, science, ELA, electives, and advisory courses. The program encourages scholars to be curious learners and stretch their academic abilities in the Academy program. Partner schools are Penn Charter, Baldwin, Agnes Irwin, Haverford, Friends? Central, Friends? Select, Episcopal, Holy Child of Rosemont, St. Peter?s, Community Partnership School, and selective charter and parochial schools.

records.Name: Mural Arts Philadelphia - 8th Street
records.Launchpad__Job_Description__c: Every summer, Mural Arts provides a paid career-exposure learning program to Philadelphia-based youth aged 14-21. This six-week intensive program introduces youth participants to hands-on work readiness experiences in what it takes to be a working artist. Through project-based learning, employing drawing, painting, photography, mixed media, and mural making, students learn to develop their own creative portfolio while working with locally and nationally known artists. Serving all youth; citywide.
